Western Cape organised crime detectives are investigating the circumstances surrounding the murder of six men in Khayelitsha on Sunday. Police spokesperson Brig Novella Potelwa said murder dockets were opened after police found the bodies of five yet-to-be identified men while a sixth person died at a medical facility. “Reports from the scene indicate police were called  to the corner of Maphongwana and Idada streets in Site C after 8pm on Sunday  where they found the bodies of  five victims who had been shot. A sixth person who had been rushed to hospital was certified dead on arrival,” said Potelwa. PODCAST | Inside Gauteng's psychiatric healthcare crisis TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.